1
00:01:40,768 --> 00:01:43,271
<i>From the day we arrive</i>

2
00:01:43,354 --> 00:01:46,357
<i>On the planet</i>

3
00:01:46,732 --> 00:01:51,237
<i>And blinking
Step into the sun</i>

4
00:01:52,530 --> 00:01:57,493
<i>There's more to see
than can ever be seen</i>

5
00:01:57,910 --> 00:02:02,665
<i>More to do
than can ever be done</i>

6
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:08,254
<i>There's far too much
to take in here</i>

7
00:02:09,422 --> 00:02:13,718
<i>More to find
than can ever be found</i>

8
00:02:15,344 --> 00:02:17,346
<i>But the sun rolling high</i>

9
00:02:18,139 --> 00:02:20,391
<i>Through the sapphire sky</i>

10
00:02:20,558 --> 00:02:25,229
<i>Keeps great and small
on the endless round</i>

11
00:02:25,396 --> 00:02:29,900
<i>It's the circle of life</i>

12
00:02:30,735 --> 00:02:35,698
<i>And it moves us all</i>

13
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:41,537
<i>Through despair and hope</i>

14
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:45,666
<i>Through faith and love</i>

15
00:02:48,085 --> 00:02:52,423
<i>Till we find our place</i>

16
00:02:53,549 --> 00:02:56,594
<i>On the path unwinding</i>

17
00:03:00,556 --> 00:03:04,393
<i>In the circle</i>

18
00:03:05,478 --> 00:03:08,689
<i>The circle of life</i>

19
00:03:56,654 --> 00:04:00,074
<i>It's the circle of life</i>

20
00:04:02,535 --> 00:04:05,579
<i>And it moves us all</i>

21
00:04:08,541 --> 00:04:12,670
<i>Through despair and hope</i>

22
00:04:14,171 --> 00:04:18,217
<i>Through faith and love</i>

23
00:04:19,885 --> 00:04:22,930
<i>Till we find our place</i>

24
00:04:25,474 --> 00:04:30,146
<i>On the path unwinding</i>

25
00:04:32,106 --> 00:04:36,694
<i>In the circle</i>

26
00:04:37,111 --> 00:04:42,074
<i>The circle of life</i>

27
00:06:01,195 --> 00:06:04,490
Life's not fair...

28
00:06:04,657 --> 00:06:06,617
is it, my little friend?

29
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:09,537
While some are
born to feast...

30
00:06:10,538 --> 00:06:13,415
others spend their lives
in the dark,

31
00:06:13,499 --> 00:06:15,167
begging for scraps.

32
00:06:17,294 --> 00:06:19,129
The way I see it...

33
00:06:19,547 --> 00:06:23,384
you and I
are exactly the same.

34
00:06:26,303 --> 00:06:28,389
We both want to
find a way out.

35
00:06:28,556 --> 00:06:30,057
The king approaches!

36
00:06:30,224 --> 00:06:31,642
This is not a drill.

37
00:06:31,809 --> 00:06:33,435
His Majesty has requested
an audience.

38
00:06:33,602 --> 00:06:37,064
Upon his entrance,
you will rise and genuflect.

39
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:38,691
Zazu...

40
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:41,694
you've made me lose my lunch.

41
00:06:42,111 --> 00:06:44,071
You will answer to Mufasa

42
00:06:44,154 --> 00:06:45,447
for missing the ceremony
this morning.

43
00:06:45,614 --> 00:06:47,908
I answer to no one.

44
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,996
Scar? Scar. Scar.

45
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:54,206
No, no.
Don't look at me like that.

46
00:06:54,373 --> 00:06:56,750
Are you hungry, Zazu?

47
00:06:56,917 --> 00:06:58,711
Perhaps we could have
a bite together!

48
00:07:00,963 --> 00:07:01,964
You can't eat me!

49
00:07:02,131 --> 00:07:05,426
It is forbidden to eat
a member of the king's court!

50
00:07:05,509 --> 00:07:07,970
Ow! No, please! Stop it!

51
00:07:08,137 --> 00:07:10,014
Scar!

52
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:15,185
Well, look who's come down
to mingle with the commoners.

53
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:20,482
Sarabi and I didn't see you
at the presentation of Simba.

54
00:07:22,151 --> 00:07:23,777
Was that today?

55
00:07:26,697 --> 00:07:28,824
Must've slipped my mind.

56
00:07:29,908 --> 00:07:31,660
Of course
I meant no disrespect

57
00:07:31,744 --> 00:07:35,122
towards His Majesty or Sarabi.

58
00:07:36,206 --> 00:07:42,421
As you know, I have tremendous
respect for the queen.

59
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:44,632
As the king's brother,

60
00:07:44,715 --> 00:07:46,425
you should've been
first in line.

61
00:07:46,592 --> 00:07:48,177
I was first in line.

62
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,512
Or don't you remember?

63
00:07:51,221 --> 00:07:54,933
That is, until the precious
prince arrived.

64
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:58,103
Don't turn your back on me,
Scar.

65
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,521
Oh, no, Mufasa,

66
00:07:59,605 --> 00:08:01,982
perhaps you shouldn't
turn your back on me.

67
00:08:03,317 --> 00:08:05,653
Is that a challenge?

68
00:08:05,819 --> 00:08:10,157
I wouldn't dream
of challenging you again.

69
00:08:11,075 --> 00:08:12,159
A wise decision.

70
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:14,578
You are no match
for His Royalness.

71
00:08:14,745 --> 00:08:17,956
Well, as far as brains go,
I got the lion's share.

72
00:08:18,999 --> 00:08:20,709
But when it comes
to brute strength,

73
00:08:20,793 --> 00:08:22,878
I'm afraid my big brother...

74
00:08:23,379 --> 00:08:24,713
will always rule.

75
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,174
Not always, Scar.

76
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:30,594
One day,
it'll be my son who rules.

77
00:08:30,761 --> 00:08:32,888
Simba will be your king.

78
00:08:33,681 --> 00:08:36,100
Then long live the king.

79
00:08:39,019 --> 00:08:41,522
- What am I gonna do with him?
- Oh, come on.

80
00:08:41,689 --> 00:08:42,815
We both know he should've been

81
00:08:42,898 --> 00:08:45,317
expelled from the Pride Lands
long ago.

82
00:08:45,484 --> 00:08:48,404
He's my brother, Zazu.
This is his home.

83
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:52,199
As long as I am king,
that will never change.

84
00:08:52,366 --> 00:08:54,034
Well, there's one
in every family, sire.

85
00:08:54,201 --> 00:08:56,453
I had a cousin who thought
he was a woodpecker.

86
00:08:56,620 --> 00:08:59,456
He slammed his head
into trees,

87
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:00,624
and our beaks
aren't built for it.

88
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:03,627
He was concussed regularly.
Oh, you've gone.

89
00:09:03,794 --> 00:09:05,838
Uh, sire, coming back!

90
00:09:05,838 --> 00:09:35,838
<b>Subtitle | www.movieddl.me</b>

91
00:10:16,658 --> 00:10:18,285
Simba.

92
00:11:02,037 --> 00:11:04,081
Dad, you awake?

93
00:11:06,416 --> 00:11:08,293
Dad, wake up!

94
00:11:09,127 --> 00:11:10,420
Dad!

95
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:13,423
Dad, Dad, Dad!

96
00:11:13,590 --> 00:11:16,301
Your son's awake.

97
00:11:16,468 --> 00:11:18,637
Before sunrise, he's your son.

98
00:11:19,054 --> 00:11:20,639
Come on, Dad, let's go.

99
00:11:20,806 --> 00:11:22,391
You said I could
patrol with you today.

100
00:11:22,474 --> 00:11:23,475
And today has started.

101
00:11:23,809 --> 00:11:26,436
You promised!
You up?

102
00:11:35,988 --> 00:11:38,490
Let's do this!

103
00:11:38,574 --> 00:11:41,368
- Let's do this.
- So, what's first?

104
00:11:41,535 --> 00:11:44,621
Give orders for the hunt?
Chase away evil intruders?

105
00:11:46,415 --> 00:11:49,376
Dad! You're going
the wrong way!

106
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:00,596
Dad?

107
00:12:00,971 --> 00:12:03,307
I'm not supposed
to go up here.

108
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:05,100
Look, Simba.

109
00:12:06,226 --> 00:12:10,063
Everything the light touches
is our kingdom.

110
00:12:10,397 --> 00:12:12,816
You rule all of that?

111
00:12:12,983 --> 00:12:14,443
Yes.

112
00:12:14,610 --> 00:12:16,987
But a king's time as ruler...

113
00:12:17,154 --> 00:12:20,073
rises and falls like the sun.

114
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,825
One day, Simba...

115
00:12:21,992 --> 00:12:24,995
the sun will set
on my time here...

116
00:12:25,162 --> 00:12:27,748
and will rise with you
as the new king.

117
00:12:29,499 --> 00:12:32,794
All of this will belong to me?

118
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:37,549
It belongs to no one,
but will be yours to protect.

119
00:12:37,716 --> 00:12:39,676
A great responsibility.

120
00:12:40,177 --> 00:12:42,179
Everything the light touches?

121
00:12:42,346 --> 00:12:46,016
Those trees?
And the watering hole?

122
00:12:46,183 --> 00:12:47,893
And that mountain?

123
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:50,354
And beyond those shadows?

124
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,522
You must not go there, Simba.

125
00:12:52,689 --> 00:12:54,900
But I thought a king could do
whatever he wants.

126
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:56,318
Take any territory.

127
00:12:57,235 --> 00:13:00,447
While others search
for what they can take...

128
00:13:00,614 --> 00:13:03,450
a true king
searches for what he can give.

129
00:13:09,706 --> 00:13:12,292
Everything you see
exists together

130
00:13:12,376 --> 00:13:14,252
in a delicate balance.

131
00:13:15,504 --> 00:13:18,715
As king, you need to
understand that balance...

132
00:13:18,882 --> 00:13:21,009
and respect
all the creatures...

133
00:13:21,176 --> 00:13:23,845
from the crawling ant
to the leaping antelope.

134
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:28,225
But, Dad,
don't we eat the antelope?

135
00:13:28,392 --> 00:13:31,979
Yes, Simba.
But let me explain.

136
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:36,358
When we die,
our bodies become the grass...

137
00:13:36,525 --> 00:13:39,444
and the antelope
eat the grass...

138
00:13:39,611 --> 00:13:44,032
and so we are all connected
in the great circle of life.

139
00:13:44,658 --> 00:13:46,743
- Sire!
- Morning, Zazu.

140
00:13:46,910 --> 00:13:48,412
Do you have
the morning report?

141
00:13:48,578 --> 00:13:50,122
Yes, sire.

142
00:13:50,205 --> 00:13:52,290
Ten flamingos
are taking a stand.

143
00:13:52,457 --> 00:13:53,875
Two giraffe
were caught necking.

144
00:13:54,042 --> 00:13:55,168
The buzz from the bees...

145
00:13:55,252 --> 00:13:56,294
is that the leopards
are in a bit of a spot.

146
00:13:56,378 --> 00:13:57,379
Ready for some fun?

147
00:13:57,462 --> 00:13:59,172
The birds are tweeting
at 4:00 in the morning.

148
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:00,924
I'm like, "Birds, we get it."

149
00:14:01,091 --> 00:14:02,592
Stay low to the ground.

150
00:14:02,718 --> 00:14:03,719
I got this.

151
00:14:03,802 --> 00:14:06,680
Check the wind,
the shadows...

152
00:14:07,389 --> 00:14:09,683
and wait for
the perfect moment to pounce.

153
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:10,934
The cheetahs stole
the baboons' dinner,

154
00:14:11,018 --> 00:14:12,060
and now the baboons
are going ape.

155
00:14:12,227 --> 00:14:14,312
Of course, as I say,
cheetahs never prosper.

156
00:14:14,479 --> 00:14:15,522
That's what I say.

157
00:14:15,605 --> 00:14:16,690
Do you get...
I'll say it again.

158
00:14:16,773 --> 00:14:18,358
Cheetahs never...

159
00:14:20,569 --> 00:14:23,780
Come on! It's the news!

160
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:28,618
That's very good!

161
00:14:30,162 --> 00:14:31,621
Sire!

162
00:14:32,581 --> 00:14:34,458
Sire!
Hyenas in the Pride Lands.

163
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:35,584
They're on the hunt!

164
00:14:35,751 --> 00:14:38,545
- Where's Sarabi?
- She's leading the charge.

165
00:14:38,712 --> 00:14:40,047
Zazu, take Simba home.

166
00:14:40,213 --> 00:14:41,882
Dad, let me come! I can help.

167
00:14:42,299 --> 00:14:45,552
No, son.
You stay with the other cubs.

168
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:48,055
I am not a cub.

169
00:14:50,474 --> 00:14:51,808
Come on.

170
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:53,685
Let's go home.

171
00:15:05,489 --> 00:15:06,740
Here we are.

172
00:15:06,907 --> 00:15:10,410
Now you go along
and play with the other cubs.

173
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,333
Great.

174
00:16:04,631 --> 00:16:06,299
If you wish
to kill something...

175
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:08,426
you might want
to stay downwind.

176
00:16:08,802 --> 00:16:10,637
I know how to hunt,
Uncle Scar.

177
00:16:10,804 --> 00:16:13,890
Well, let's hope we're never
attacked by a beetle.

178
00:16:14,057 --> 00:16:17,686
Go back to your den, Simba.
I don't babysit.

179
00:16:17,978 --> 00:16:20,730
Babysit? I'm gonna be the king
of Pride Rock.

180
00:16:23,191 --> 00:16:24,943
My dad showed me
the whole kingdom.

181
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:27,154
Said I'm going to rule it all.

182
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:28,905
Is that so?

183
00:16:29,072 --> 00:16:30,115
Think about it.

184
00:16:30,282 --> 00:16:33,243
When I'm king,
I'll have to give you orders.

185
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:35,162
Tell you what to do.

186
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:37,164
How weird is that?

187
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:40,375
You've no idea.

188
00:16:42,085 --> 00:16:45,172
So, your dad showed you
the whole kingdom?

189
00:16:45,839 --> 00:16:49,092
Did he show you the shadows
beyond the northern borders?

190
00:16:49,259 --> 00:16:53,346
No. He said I can't go there.
Ever.

191
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:57,309
And he's absolutely right.

192
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:02,480
An elephant graveyard is
no place for a young prince.

193
00:17:02,647 --> 00:17:06,359
An elephant graveyard? Whoa.

194
00:17:07,027 --> 00:17:09,571
Oh, dear. I've said too much.

195
00:17:09,738 --> 00:17:11,615
Though I suppose you'd have
found out sooner or later...

196
00:17:11,781 --> 00:17:14,534
you being king and all.

197
00:17:14,701 --> 00:17:16,036
You've been there?

198
00:17:16,203 --> 00:17:19,539
We've all been there.
And it's no place for a cub.

199
00:17:19,706 --> 00:17:22,042
All those rotting bones...

200
00:17:22,209 --> 00:17:25,295
and burning pools
of oozing mud.

201
00:17:25,462 --> 00:17:27,631
Rotting bones?
Oozing mud?

202
00:17:27,797 --> 00:17:31,092
Promise me
you'll stay away, Simba.

203
00:17:31,259 --> 00:17:32,844
Now, you run along.

204
00:17:36,514 --> 00:17:38,350
And remember...

205
00:17:40,101 --> 00:17:42,729
it's our little secret...

206
00:17:44,272 --> 00:17:45,982
Your Majesty.

207
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:55,575
Nala! Come on.
We have to go.

208
00:17:55,742 --> 00:17:57,452
- Where?
- Watering hole.

209
00:17:57,619 --> 00:17:59,621
Simba, she's having her bath.

210
00:17:59,788 --> 00:18:01,623
And it's time for yours.

211
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:02,958
But, Mom...

212
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:04,960
I can do it myself.

213
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:06,378
Hold still.

214
00:18:06,544 --> 00:18:08,213
You're messing up my mane!

215
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:10,257
Come on. Behind the ears.

216
00:18:10,423 --> 00:18:12,175
Come on, Mom!

217
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:17,555
See? All clean. Can we go?

218
00:18:17,722 --> 00:18:21,226
There's no hyenas.
You just chased them all off.

219
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:25,313
Just to the watering hole
and no further.

220
00:18:26,648 --> 00:18:28,525
And stay downwind.

221
00:18:28,692 --> 00:18:30,568
And one more little thing.

222
00:18:30,735 --> 00:18:32,529
Zazu will be going with you.

223
00:18:32,696 --> 00:18:33,738
Zazu?

224
00:18:33,822 --> 00:18:34,823
Zazu goes...

225
00:18:34,906 --> 00:18:36,491
or you don't.

226
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:43,748
Come along. Keep up.
Let's move in a unit.

227
00:18:43,915 --> 00:18:45,417
Okay, buddy system.

228
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:47,252
So, where are we really going?

229
00:18:47,419 --> 00:18:48,420
How did you know?

230
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:49,587
You hate the water.

231
00:18:49,754 --> 00:18:51,923
I heard
about this place, Nala.

232
00:18:52,007 --> 00:18:53,550
The most incredible,
amazing...

233
00:18:53,717 --> 00:18:55,427
Just tell me where.

234
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:58,388
An elephant graveyard.

235
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:00,682
Whoa. How far is it?

236
00:19:00,849 --> 00:19:02,684
Not far. Just to the shadows.

237
00:19:02,851 --> 00:19:04,728
But don't worry,
everyone's been there.

238
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:06,229
We've never been
that far before.

239
00:19:06,396 --> 00:19:08,273
- What if we get lost?
- Relax, Nala.

240
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:11,901
I patrolled the entire kingdom
this morning with my dad.

241
00:19:12,068 --> 00:19:13,528
There's nothing
to worry about.

242
00:19:13,695 --> 00:19:15,572
Well, there is one thing.

243
00:19:16,656 --> 00:19:19,200
We have an imminent threat.
Something is approaching.

244
00:19:19,367 --> 00:19:21,286
Oh, wait, scratch that.
That's my own shadow.

245
00:19:21,578 --> 00:19:23,330
How we getting rid
of the dodo?

246
00:19:23,496 --> 00:19:25,123
Trust me, I got this.

247
00:19:25,290 --> 00:19:26,624
Follow me to freedom.

248
00:19:28,043 --> 00:19:29,919
Oh, how lovely it is...

249
00:19:30,086 --> 00:19:33,298
to see the future king
with his future queen.

250
00:19:33,465 --> 00:19:35,216
I could just molt.

251
00:19:35,383 --> 00:19:37,010
What do you mean,
"future queen"?

252
00:19:37,177 --> 00:19:40,013
Well, one day the two of you
will be betrothed.

253
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:42,974
Intended. Affianced.

254
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:45,185
Simba, you speak bird?

255
00:19:45,352 --> 00:19:46,436
Married!

256
00:19:46,603 --> 00:19:48,897
Come on.
One day you will be married.

257
00:19:51,483 --> 00:19:52,817
To each other.

258
00:19:53,193 --> 00:19:54,277
- Ugh!
- Ew!

259
00:19:54,736 --> 00:19:56,237
Mmm-mmm. That's not
gonna happen, Zazu.

260
00:19:56,321 --> 00:19:57,322
Never ever.

261
