00:36:31,565 --> 00:36:33,192
<i>Be prepared
Be prepared</i>

518
00:36:33,359 --> 00:36:35,402
<i>- Be prepared
- Be prepared</i>

519
00:36:35,569 --> 00:36:37,196
<i>Be prepared
Be prepared</i>

520
00:36:37,363 --> 00:36:41,158
<i>Be prepared</i>

521
00:36:45,412 --> 00:36:47,456
<i>Be prepared</i>

522
00:36:49,541 --> 00:36:53,504
<i>Yes, our teeth and ambitions
are bared</i>

523
00:36:53,670 --> 00:36:57,091
<i>Be prepared</i>

524
00:37:17,694 --> 00:37:19,905
My dad was pretty upset
with me.

525
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:22,157
That's why we're here, Simba.

526
00:37:22,324 --> 00:37:25,202
I think I know a way for you
to make it up to him.

527
00:37:25,369 --> 00:37:28,747
A gift that will make him
forget it ever happened.

528
00:37:28,914 --> 00:37:31,792
But he's the king.
What could I give him?

529
00:37:31,959 --> 00:37:33,502
Your roar.

530
00:37:33,669 --> 00:37:34,670
My roar?

531
00:37:34,837 --> 00:37:36,213
Yes!

532
00:37:37,172 --> 00:37:38,799
Did you hear that?

533
00:37:39,174 --> 00:37:43,804
This gorge is where all lions
come to find their roar.

534
00:37:43,971 --> 00:37:44,972
All lions?

535
00:37:45,472 --> 00:37:46,765
Even my dad?

536
00:37:47,182 --> 00:37:50,102
Even Mufasa came here
when he was your age.

537
00:37:50,269 --> 00:37:51,687
Refused to leave...

538
00:37:51,854 --> 00:37:55,732
until his roar could be heard
above the rim.

539
00:37:56,567 --> 00:37:57,943
All the way up there?

540
00:37:58,110 --> 00:37:59,987
That's when you know
you've found it.

541
00:38:00,154 --> 00:38:01,905
With a little practice...

542
00:38:02,072 --> 00:38:04,908
you'll never be called
a cub again.

543
00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:07,244
Watch this.

544
00:38:09,413 --> 00:38:11,373
You'll get it, Simba.

545
00:38:11,540 --> 00:38:13,709
Just takes time.

546
00:38:13,876 --> 00:38:15,544
I'll check on you later.

547
00:38:16,503 --> 00:38:19,089
Dad will be so proud,
won't he?

548
00:38:19,256 --> 00:38:21,884
It's a gift
he'll never forget.

549
00:40:07,197 --> 00:40:08,782
Mufasa! Quick!

550
00:40:08,949 --> 00:40:10,659
Stampede in the gorge!

551
00:40:10,826 --> 00:40:11,994
Simba's down there!

552
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:13,412
Simba?

553
00:40:14,162 --> 00:40:15,581
I'll find him.

554
00:40:42,774 --> 00:40:43,775
Zazu!

555
00:40:44,151 --> 00:40:46,612
Hold on!
Help is coming!

556
00:40:53,702 --> 00:40:56,079
There he is!
On that tree!

557
00:40:59,750 --> 00:41:01,960
I'm coming, Simba!
Hold on!

558
00:41:07,424 --> 00:41:10,052
I'll help them, Zazu!
You get the pride!

559
00:41:10,218 --> 00:41:11,428
Go!

560
00:41:37,204 --> 00:41:38,246
Dad!

561
00:41:39,206 --> 00:41:40,248
Simba!

562
00:41:40,999 --> 00:41:42,709
Come to me, son.

563
00:41:43,168 --> 00:41:44,378
Jump!

564
00:42:03,730 --> 00:42:05,982
Dad!

565
00:43:01,371 --> 00:43:02,581
Scar!

566
00:43:05,459 --> 00:43:06,752
Help me.

567
00:43:14,676 --> 00:43:18,096
Long live the king!

568
00:43:24,686 --> 00:43:27,022
No!

569
00:43:45,665 --> 00:43:46,750
Dad?

570
00:43:55,300 --> 00:43:56,718
Dad?

571
00:44:22,869 --> 00:44:24,287
Dad?

572
00:44:28,416 --> 00:44:29,835
Dad?

573
00:44:41,471 --> 00:44:43,557
Come on, wake up.

574
00:44:49,729 --> 00:44:54,150
Help! Somebody help!

575
00:45:25,432 --> 00:45:27,058
Simba!

576
00:45:27,559 --> 00:45:29,728
What have you done?

577
00:45:31,688 --> 00:45:33,481
It was a stampede.

578
00:45:33,648 --> 00:45:35,025
He tried to save me.

579
00:45:35,191 --> 00:45:37,402
It was an accident.

580
00:45:37,736 --> 00:45:40,488
- I didn't mean for it to...
- Of course you didn't.

581
00:45:40,655 --> 00:45:44,075
No one ever means
for these things to happen.

582
00:45:44,242 --> 00:45:45,952
But the king is dead...

583
00:45:46,119 --> 00:45:47,746
and if it weren't for you...

584
00:45:49,372 --> 00:45:51,625
he'd still be alive.

585
00:45:51,791 --> 00:45:54,544
Your father had such hopes
for you...

586
00:45:54,711 --> 00:45:57,881
gave you so many chances.

587
00:45:58,048 --> 00:46:00,008
And this is how you repay him.

588
00:46:00,634 --> 00:46:03,261
I didn't know.
I didn't know.

589
00:46:03,428 --> 00:46:05,305
Oh, what will
your mother think?

590
00:46:05,472 --> 00:46:08,850
A son who causes
his father's death.

591
00:46:09,017 --> 00:46:13,605
A boy who kills a king.

592
00:46:14,356 --> 00:46:16,608
What am I gonna do?

593
00:46:17,734 --> 00:46:18,944
Run.

594
00:46:19,486 --> 00:46:22,322
Run away, Simba.

595
00:46:22,739 --> 00:46:26,201
Run away and never return!

596
00:46:38,338 --> 00:46:40,548
Kill him.

597
00:47:18,294 --> 00:47:21,297
Go down
and make sure he's dead.

598
00:47:29,097 --> 00:47:30,432
Seriously?

599
00:47:30,515 --> 00:47:32,267
Oh, I'm sorry.

600
00:47:34,811 --> 00:47:36,104
That's a good distance
right there.

601
00:47:36,187 --> 00:47:37,230
Okay.

602
00:47:39,399 --> 00:47:41,943
No little cub
could survive that fall.

603
00:47:42,569 --> 00:47:44,070
Listen,
we're gonna tell her...

604
00:47:44,237 --> 00:47:47,198
we went down there
and we ate him.

605
00:47:47,282 --> 00:47:49,117
Uh-huh. That's perfect,
'cause I am starving!

606
00:47:49,284 --> 00:47:50,827
We're not gonna eat him.

607
00:47:50,994 --> 00:47:52,162
Simba is dead.

608
00:47:52,328 --> 00:47:54,748
That's all she ever
has to know.

609
00:47:56,666 --> 00:47:58,001
Works for me.

610
00:48:52,347 --> 00:48:57,310
Mufasa's death
is a terrible tragedy.

611
00:48:57,685 --> 00:49:00,480
The greatest leader
the pride has ever known.

612
00:49:01,147 --> 00:49:03,149
To lose a brother...

613
00:49:03,650 --> 00:49:08,279
such a deep, personal loss.

614
00:49:09,239 --> 00:49:12,992
And little Simba,
who had barely begun to live.

615
00:49:13,159 --> 00:49:16,704
A cub whose blood
held our future.

616
00:49:16,871 --> 00:49:20,041
It's almost too much
to endure.

617
00:49:21,084 --> 00:49:24,212
I only wish I had gotten
to the gorge in time...

618
00:49:24,379 --> 00:49:27,382
been there to save them.

619
00:49:28,633 --> 00:49:33,054
And so it is
with a heavy heart...

620
00:49:33,680 --> 00:49:35,849
that I must assume the throne.

621
00:49:36,391 --> 00:49:39,102
Mufasa and Simba are gone...

622
00:49:39,269 --> 00:49:43,189
which means I am your king.

623
00:49:45,817 --> 00:49:47,110
But I must admit...

624
00:49:47,277 --> 00:49:50,029
I cannot bear
this burden alone.

625
00:49:51,489 --> 00:49:53,700
And I will need some help...

626
00:49:53,867 --> 00:49:55,869
to ensure

627
00:49:55,952 --> 00:49:57,996
the safety of the pride.

628
00:50:05,461 --> 00:50:08,506
Nala, stay close.

629
00:50:08,798 --> 00:50:12,844
And so, from the ashes
of this tragedy...

630
00:50:13,011 --> 00:50:17,182
we shall welcome
the dawning of a new era.

631
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:18,975
A great...

632
00:50:19,851 --> 00:50:23,021
and glorious future!

633
00:50:33,364 --> 00:50:35,366
Oh, dear.

634
00:52:20,638 --> 00:52:21,931
I missed 'em!

635
00:52:22,098 --> 00:52:23,808
I'm gonna get one of
those vultures one day.

636
00:52:23,975 --> 00:52:24,976
I'm gonna get one!

637
00:52:25,059 --> 00:52:26,644
I don't know why it's
so important to you.

638
00:52:26,811 --> 00:52:29,022
I just feel like it would
make me feel better.

639
00:52:29,105 --> 00:52:31,190
Oh, no.
It's a little lion!

640
00:52:31,357 --> 00:52:33,318
- That is not a lion.
- Well then, go check it out.

641
00:52:33,401 --> 00:52:34,444
- What is it?
- That is not a lion,

642
00:52:34,527 --> 00:52:35,570
it's a furry bird!

643
00:52:35,653 --> 00:52:36,863
It looks like a lion!

644
00:52:37,030 --> 00:52:39,741
That's not a lion. Let me get
a closer look. Excuse me.

645
00:52:39,824 --> 00:52:42,452
All right, let me see
what we're dealing with here.

646
00:52:42,618 --> 00:52:43,619
It's a lion!

647
00:52:43,786 --> 00:52:45,121
- Run for your life, Pumbaa!
- Wait! Hey, Timon.

648
00:52:45,288 --> 00:52:47,999
Wait, Timon, wait!
It's a little lion!

649
00:52:48,166 --> 00:52:49,375
It gets bigger.

650
00:52:49,542 --> 00:52:51,377
Can we keep him?
Can we please keep him?

651
00:52:51,544 --> 00:52:53,421
Oh, oh, okay. I promise
I'll walk him every day!

652
00:52:53,588 --> 00:52:54,881
If he makes a little mess,
I'll clean it up.

653
00:52:55,048 --> 00:52:56,132
You'll be his little mess!

654
00:52:56,299 --> 00:52:58,343
He's gonna eat you and then
use my body as a toothpick!

655
00:52:58,509 --> 00:53:00,470
But one day,
when he's big and strong,

656
00:53:00,553 --> 00:53:01,804
he'll be on our side!

657
00:53:01,971 --> 00:53:04,307
I've got it.
What if he's on our side?

658
00:53:04,474 --> 00:53:05,683
Hear me out!

659
00:53:05,850 --> 00:53:09,854
Having a ferocious lion around
might not be such a bad idea!

660
00:53:10,021 --> 00:53:11,314
Well then, can we keep him?

661
00:53:11,481 --> 00:53:12,732
Yes, of course
we can keep him!

662
00:53:12,899 --> 00:53:15,443
My God, who is the brains
of this operation?

663
00:53:15,610 --> 00:53:17,403
<i>We're gonna name him Fred!</i>

664
00:53:17,570 --> 00:53:19,322
Who are you?

665
00:53:20,406 --> 00:53:21,532
Uh, we're the guys
who saved your life.

666
00:53:21,616 --> 00:53:22,617
Yes.

667
00:53:22,700 --> 00:53:24,911
Risked everything.
Fought off angry vultures!

668
00:53:25,078 --> 00:53:26,704
Hordes of them. Flocks.

669
00:53:26,871 --> 00:53:28,206
I'm Pumbaa.

670
00:53:28,373 --> 00:53:29,624
- This is Timon.
- Did I mention

671
00:53:29,707 --> 00:53:30,958
that we saved your life?

672
00:53:31,209 --> 00:53:33,169
It doesn't matter.

673
00:53:34,962 --> 00:53:37,215
Whoa. How bleak is that?

674
00:53:37,298 --> 00:53:38,341
It doesn't even matter?

675
00:53:38,424 --> 00:53:40,593
Like I don't have enough
that I'm dealing with, right?

676
00:53:40,760 --> 00:53:42,178
Now his problems
are my problems?

677
00:53:42,345 --> 00:53:44,013
But we can help him. We're
in a position to help him.

678
00:53:44,680 --> 00:53:48,518
So, how are you,
in as few words as possible?

679
00:53:48,976 --> 00:53:50,895
I did something terrible.

680
00:53:51,062 --> 00:53:52,897
I don't wanna talk about it.

681
00:53:53,064 --> 00:53:55,691
Look, kid,
we've all made mistakes.

682
00:53:55,775 --> 00:53:58,486
Uh, there must be something
we can do, right?

683
00:53:58,653 --> 00:54:00,655
Not unless you can change
the past.

684
00:54:00,822 --> 00:54:02,156
Well, you know,
that's a lot to ask...

685
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:03,282
That's pretty hard.
That's a biggie.

686
00:54:03,366 --> 00:54:04,367
...if I'm being honest.

687
00:54:04,450 --> 00:54:05,993
I mean, change the past?
It already happened.

688
00:54:06,160 --> 00:54:07,829
Yeah, so you can't
change that.

689
00:54:07,995 --> 00:54:09,288
But you know
what you can change?

690
00:54:10,289 --> 00:54:12,333
The future.
That's our specialty.

691
00:54:12,500 --> 00:54:13,835
Kind of our thing.

692
00:54:14,001 --> 00:54:16,421
How can you change something
that hasn't happened?

693
00:54:16,587 --> 00:54:18,673
Well, to change the future,

694
00:54:18,756 --> 00:54:20,216
you gotta put your past
behind you.

695
00:54:20,383 --> 00:54:21,384
Way behind.

696
00:54:21,467 --> 00:54:23,761
Look, kid, bad things happen

697
00:54:23,845 --> 00:54:26,013
and you can't do anything
about it, right?

698
00:54:26,097 --> 00:54:27,098
Right.

699
00:54:27,223 --> 00:54:29,809
Wrong! When the world
turns its back on you...

700
00:54:29,976 --> 00:54:31,769
