on the world!

701
00:54:32,353 --> 00:54:34,147
And only embrace what's next!

702
00:54:34,313 --> 00:54:36,190
And turn the "what"
into "so what?"

703
00:54:36,357 --> 00:54:38,484
Well, that's not
what I was taught.

704
00:54:38,651 --> 00:54:40,528
Well, then maybe
you need a new lesson.

705
00:54:40,695 --> 00:54:45,158
Repeat after me, kid.
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

706
00:54:45,741 --> 00:54:47,660
- What?
- <i>Hakuna matata.</i>

707
00:54:47,827 --> 00:54:49,203
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

708
00:54:49,370 --> 00:54:50,413
Most people
get a bigger reaction

709
00:54:50,496 --> 00:54:51,581
when we say it the first...

710
00:54:51,747 --> 00:54:53,166
Okay, well anyway.
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

711
00:54:53,249 --> 00:54:54,625
Some people
start clapping immediately.

712
00:54:54,792 --> 00:54:57,044
It means "no worries."
One and a...

713
00:54:57,211 --> 00:54:59,255
I do the counting here.

714
00:54:59,422 --> 00:55:01,257
- I wanna count!
- Why don't we count together?

715
00:55:01,424 --> 00:55:02,508
- Okay, that's a good idea.
- All right.

716
00:55:02,925 --> 00:55:04,302
One and a two and a...

717
00:55:04,844 --> 00:55:06,471
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

718
00:55:07,472 --> 00:55:09,807
<i>What a wonderful phrase</i>

719
00:55:10,516 --> 00:55:12,351
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

720
00:55:12,935 --> 00:55:16,355
<i>It ain't no passing craze</i>

721
00:55:16,856 --> 00:55:21,486
<i>It means no worries
For the rest of your days</i>

722
00:55:22,487 --> 00:55:24,697
<i>It's our problem-free</i>

723
00:55:25,615 --> 00:55:27,658
<i>Philosophy</i>

724
00:55:27,992 --> 00:55:30,995
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

725
00:55:32,038 --> 00:55:34,874
<i>- Hakuna matata?</i>
- Yeah, it's our motto.

726
00:55:35,208 --> 00:55:36,542
What's a motto?

727
00:55:36,626 --> 00:55:37,960
Nothin'.
What's-a-motto with you?

728
00:55:38,127 --> 00:55:39,253
- Nice.
- Boom!

729
00:55:39,420 --> 00:55:41,839
Those two words
will solve all your problems.

730
00:55:42,006 --> 00:55:44,425
Yeah. Take Pumbaa here.

731
00:55:44,717 --> 00:55:48,346
<i>Why,
when he was a young warthog</i>

732
00:55:48,513 --> 00:55:51,724
<i>When I was a young warthog</i>

733
00:55:53,476 --> 00:55:55,561
- How are you feeling?
- It's an emotional story.

734
00:55:55,728 --> 00:55:58,356
<i>He found his aroma
lacked a certain appeal</i>

735
00:55:58,523 --> 00:56:01,400
<i>He could clear the savannah
after every meal</i>

736
00:56:01,567 --> 00:56:03,611
<i>I'm a sensitive soul</i>

737
00:56:03,694 --> 00:56:07,198
<i>Although I seem thick-skinned</i>

738
00:56:08,282 --> 00:56:13,162
<i>And it hurt that my friends
never stood downwind</i>

739
00:56:13,329 --> 00:56:15,581
I was always here for you
and I resent that.

740
00:56:15,748 --> 00:56:18,251
<i>-And, oh, the shame
- Yes, he was ashamed</i>

741
00:56:18,417 --> 00:56:19,961
<i>I thought of changing my name</i>

742
00:56:20,127 --> 00:56:21,629
I mean, to what, "Brad"?

743
00:56:21,796 --> 00:56:24,507
<i>And I got downhearted</i>

744
00:56:25,007 --> 00:56:27,426
<i>Ev'ry time that I farted</i>

745
00:56:27,593 --> 00:56:28,886
Are you gonna stop me?

746
00:56:29,053 --> 00:56:31,931
No, I'm not! You disgust me!

747
00:56:32,014 --> 00:56:33,766
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

748
00:56:34,559 --> 00:56:37,144
<i>What a wonderful phrase</i>

749
00:56:37,770 --> 00:56:39,480
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

750
00:56:40,022 --> 00:56:42,400
<i>Ain't no passing craze</i>

751
00:56:43,317 --> 00:56:47,780
<i>It means no worries
For the rest of your days</i>

752
00:56:47,947 --> 00:56:49,198
<i>Yeah, sing it, kid</i>

753
00:56:49,448 --> 00:56:52,451
<i>It's our problem-free</i>

754
00:56:52,535 --> 00:56:54,829
<i>Philosophy</i>

755
00:56:54,996 --> 00:56:56,872
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

756
00:57:00,751 --> 00:57:02,753
Welcome to
our humble home.

757
00:57:02,920 --> 00:57:04,171
You live here?

758
00:57:04,338 --> 00:57:05,631
Well, we live
wherever we want.

759
00:57:05,798 --> 00:57:07,091
We do as we please.

760
00:57:07,258 --> 00:57:08,301
It's beautiful.

761
00:57:08,467 --> 00:57:10,469
Yeah,
it's really nice, huh?

762
00:57:11,095 --> 00:57:13,931
Everyone, this is Simba.

763
00:57:14,140 --> 00:57:16,017
That, my friend, is a lion.

764
00:57:16,183 --> 00:57:17,310
What about food?

765
00:57:17,393 --> 00:57:18,519
Have you thought
about feeding that thing?

766
00:57:18,686 --> 00:57:21,188
Yeah, I'm starved!
I could eat a whole zebra.

767
00:57:21,272 --> 00:57:22,356
Here we go.

768
00:57:22,648 --> 00:57:25,318
Uh, no, no, no, kid,
we're fresh out of zebra.

769
00:57:25,484 --> 00:57:26,652
Any antelope?

770
00:57:26,819 --> 00:57:28,571
- Uh-oh.
- No, listen, kid...

771
00:57:28,738 --> 00:57:30,823
if you want to live with us,
you have to eat like us.

772
00:57:30,990 --> 00:57:33,868
And most importantly,
not eat us!

773
00:57:34,368 --> 00:57:37,455
This looks like a good
spot to rustle up some grub!

774
00:57:39,498 --> 00:57:40,499
- Yeah!
- It's perfect!

775
00:57:40,666 --> 00:57:41,876
Step aside, fellas!

776
00:57:41,959 --> 00:57:43,336
Ugh. What's that?

777
00:57:43,502 --> 00:57:44,545
Ooh. Too chewy.

778
00:57:44,712 --> 00:57:46,130
This one's got some nuttiness!

779
00:57:46,213 --> 00:57:48,758
Mmm. Now that's what
I call umami!

780
00:57:48,841 --> 00:57:51,302
Slimy, yet satisfying.

781
00:57:51,385 --> 00:57:52,428
Mmm. Extra crunchy.

782
00:57:52,511 --> 00:57:53,971
- They're local.
- Yeah. Oh, are they?

783
00:57:54,138 --> 00:57:55,222
They're from right there.

784
00:57:55,389 --> 00:57:57,642
I'm telling ya, kid,
this is the great life.

785
00:57:57,808 --> 00:57:58,809
No rules.

786
00:57:58,976 --> 00:58:00,853
No responsibilities.

787
00:58:00,936 --> 00:58:03,564
Ooh!
The little cream-filled kind.

788
00:58:03,648 --> 00:58:04,815
I love these!

789
00:58:04,899 --> 00:58:05,941
- Those are good.
- I love these.

790
00:58:06,025 --> 00:58:07,026
Those are the best.

791
00:58:07,109 --> 00:58:08,110
Can I have the head?

792
00:58:08,194 --> 00:58:09,195
Well, kid?

793
00:58:10,363 --> 00:58:11,781
Oh, well.

794
00:58:12,031 --> 00:58:13,616
<i>Hakuna matata.</i>

795
00:58:16,827 --> 00:58:18,412
Slimy...

796
00:58:19,330 --> 00:58:21,957
yet satisfying.

797
00:58:22,124 --> 00:58:23,709
- That's it!
- We didn't lie!

798
00:58:23,876 --> 00:58:26,504
Egg sac!
I got an egg sac!

799
00:58:29,423 --> 00:58:30,758
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

800
00:58:30,841 --> 00:58:32,051
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

801
00:58:32,218 --> 00:58:34,762
<i>Hakuna matata
Hakuna matata</i>

802
00:58:34,929 --> 00:58:37,556
<i>Hakuna matata
Hakuna matata</i>

803
00:58:37,723 --> 00:58:39,141
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

804
00:58:39,767 --> 00:58:44,730
<i>It means no worries
For the rest of your days</i>

805
00:58:45,898 --> 00:58:48,818
<i>It's our problem-free</i>

806
00:58:48,984 --> 00:58:51,362
<i>Philosophy</i>

807
00:58:51,529 --> 00:58:54,490
<i>-Hakuna matata, oh
- Hakuna matata, hakuna matata</i>

808
00:58:54,657 --> 00:58:57,118
<i>-Hakuna matata, yeah
- Hakuna matata, hakuna matata</i>

809
00:58:57,368 --> 00:59:00,496
<i>-Hakuna matata
- Hakuna matata, hakuna matata</i>

810
00:59:00,871 --> 00:59:02,832
<i>Hakuna matata
Hakuna matata</i>

811
00:59:02,998 --> 00:59:05,042
<i>-It means no worries
- Hakuna matata</i>

812
00:59:05,209 --> 00:59:07,712
<i>-For the rest of your days
- Hakuna matata, hakuna matata</i>

813
00:59:07,795 --> 00:59:08,838
<i>Hakuna</i>

814
00:59:08,921 --> 00:59:11,674
<i>It's our problem-free</i>

815
00:59:11,841 --> 00:59:14,009
<i>Philosophy</i>

816
00:59:14,385 --> 00:59:16,637
<i>Hakuna matata</i>

817
00:59:16,804 --> 00:59:17,805
One more time.

818
00:59:17,888 --> 00:59:19,014
Oh, no,
I think we did it. Yeah.

819
00:59:19,098 --> 00:59:20,099
I think we got this one.

820
00:59:20,182 --> 00:59:21,225
But we're just getting
in the groove, guys.

821
00:59:21,308 --> 00:59:22,309
No, let's leave 'em
wanting more.

822
00:59:22,476 --> 00:59:24,019
Yeah, you've grown
400 pounds since we started.

823
00:59:24,186 --> 00:59:25,855
Meanwhile I look
exactly the same.

824
00:59:26,021 --> 00:59:27,148
<i>It means no worries</i>

825
00:59:27,231 --> 00:59:28,274
Will you tell him
to stop?

826
00:59:28,357 --> 00:59:29,400
But you insisted
we sing the song.

827
00:59:29,483 --> 00:59:30,568
I insisted?
You started singing it!

828
00:59:30,651 --> 00:59:31,652
Well,
it's our signature song...

829
00:59:31,736 --> 00:59:32,778
we shouldn't be sharing it
with everyone.

830
00:59:32,862 --> 00:59:33,863
Look at that sunset.

831
00:59:33,946 --> 00:59:35,030
But it's our signature
song, so we have to.

832
00:59:35,114 --> 00:59:37,158
Look, just tell him to stop.

833
00:59:37,324 --> 00:59:38,826
<i>It means no worries</i>

834
00:59:38,909 --> 00:59:40,035
Oh, now he's riffing,
Pumbaa.

835
00:59:40,119 --> 00:59:41,162
This is a nightmare.

836
00:59:41,245 --> 00:59:42,788
It actually is
becoming better and better.

837
01:00:17,531 --> 01:00:18,949
Nala.

838
01:00:19,700 --> 01:00:20,701
Come.

839
01:00:21,118 --> 01:00:22,453
Sit with us.

840
01:00:31,670 --> 01:00:34,089
Zazu, where have you been?

841
01:00:34,465 --> 01:00:37,927
I'm sorry, Nala.
I came as soon as I could.

842
01:00:42,473 --> 01:00:44,099
The morning report, Zazu.

843
01:00:44,475 --> 01:00:47,478
Your Majesty, the Pride Lands
are in imminent danger.

844
01:00:47,645 --> 01:00:50,606
The hyenas are chasing off
the last of the herds.

845
01:00:50,773 --> 01:00:51,857
The bird's back!

846
01:00:53,484 --> 01:00:54,902
Get him!

847
01:00:58,906 --> 01:01:01,951
Don't come here again,
unless you want to be eaten!

848
01:01:25,307 --> 01:01:28,310
We have to do something,
Sarabi. We have to fight!

849
01:01:28,519 --> 01:01:32,064
Nala. Scar is the king.

850
01:01:32,273 --> 01:01:33,899
But you are our queen!

851
01:01:34,066 --> 01:01:36,151
We should leave
before it's too late!

852
01:01:36,318 --> 01:01:40,447
We must all stay together
and protect the Pride Lands.

853
01:01:40,614 --> 01:01:44,159
This is our home.
We must never abandon it.

854
01:01:44,326 --> 01:01:46,328
This isn't the home
I remember.

855
01:01:46,495 --> 01:01:49,206
Our time will come, Nala.

856
01:01:49,373 --> 01:01:50,583
Be patient.

857
01:01:50,749 --> 01:01:52,167
Sarabi.

858
01:01:53,878 --> 01:01:55,671
The king wishes to see you.

859
01:01:56,505 --> 01:01:58,132
Don't go.

860
01:01:59,341 --> 01:02:01,760
I'm not afraid of him.

861
01:02:16,984 --> 01:02:19,278
Won't you join me, Sarabi?

862
01:02:19,445 --> 01:02:21,322
There's plenty to go around.

863
01:02:21,614 --> 01:02:23,365
You're over hunting, Scar.

864
01:02:23,532 --> 01:02:25,576
I've simply perfected
the kill.

865
01:02:26,493 --> 01:02:27,995
With the help of my army.

866
01:02:28,162 --> 01:02:30,331
You're killing everything.

867
01:02:30,831 --> 01:02:33,959
Don't you see? There is nobody
to challenge me.

868
01:02:34,126 --> 01:02:36,503
We can finally take
whatever we want.

869
01:02:37,129 --> 01:02:38,547
We?

870
01:02:38,714 --> 01:02:42,343
Long ago
you chose Mufasa over me.

871
01:02:42,509 --> 01:02:44,470
But now there is a new king.

872
01:02:45,012 --> 01:02:47,139
So stop being so selfish.

873
01:02:47,556 --> 01:02:49,308
You are the selfish one.

874
01:02:49,475 --> 01:02:51,435
The other lions look to you.

875
01:02:51,602 --> 01:02:54,521
As long as you resist
they will reject me.

876
01:02:55,397 --> 01:02:59,902
Take your place by my side,
and we will feast together.

877
01:03:00,444 --> 01:03:03,405
I will never be your queen!

878
01:03:05,157 --> 01:03:06,825
Then from now on...

879
01:03:06,992 --> 01:03:11,121
the lions will eat
after the hyenas.

880
01:03:11,372 --> 01:03:13,958
And they don't
leave much behind.

881
01:04:43,922 --> 01:04:44,923
Just what do you think

882
01:04:45,007 --> 01:04:46,967
you are doing, young lady?

883
01:04:47,134 --> 01:04:48,510
Go away, Zazu.

884
01:04:48,677 --> 01:04:50,387
I'm going to find help.

885
01:04:50,554 --> 01:04:52,306
I will very much not go away.

886
01:04:52,473 --> 01:04:55,934
I am sworn to protect you and
must order you back to bed.

887
01:04:56,101 --> 01:04:58,771
I don't need
protecting anymore.

888
01:05:49,154 --> 01:05:51,824
Uh, Scar!
Uh, wonderful to see you.

889
01:05:52,074 --> 01:05:53,992
Uh,
sorry to drop in like this!

890
01:05:54,076 --> 01:05:55,119
Ah!

891
01:05:55,661 --> 01:05:58,455
Have I ever told you
about my brother

892
01:05:58,539 --> 01:06:00,624
who thought he was
a woodpecker?

893
01:06:14,263 --> 01:06:15,889
Nala...

894
01:06:39,913 --> 01:06:41,290
Oh, I'm gonna get ya!

895
01:06:41,456 --> 01:06:43,167
I'm gonna get ya!
Oh, I got ya!

896
01:06:43,250 --> 01:06:44,751
Oh.

897
01:06:44,918 --> 01:06:46,795
Simba! It's you!

898
01:06:46,879 --> 01:06:48,255
Did you see that?

899
01:06:48,338 --> 01:06:49,715
Man, that butterfly
was right there!

900
01:06:49,882 --> 01:06:51,008
I almost had him.

901
01:06:51,341 --> 01:06:52,634
I thought it was a lion.

902
01:06:52,718 --> 01:06:54,052
You know,
the other kind of lion.

903
01:06:54,511 --> 01:06:55,846
You know, a real lion?

904
01:06:56,013 --> 01:06:57,598
I mean, not that
you're not a real lion.

905
01:06:57,681 --> 01:06:59,516
But you know,
the kind that eats...

906
01:06:59,683 --> 01:07:00,893
I'm gonna go.

907
01:07:01,810 --> 01:07:03,437
Hey, where you going?

908
01:07:03,604 --> 01:07:05,814
You wanna get some grubs?

909
01:07:08,692 --> 01:07:10,360
What's up with that guy?

910
01:07:10,444 --> 01:07:11,445
Um, Simba...

911
01:07:12,154 --> 01:07:13,906
How can I say this?

912
01:07:14,072 --> 01:07:15,824
- He's prey.
- Yeah.

913
01:07:15,991 --> 01:07:20,078
And he is never gonna want to
frolic with a carnivore.

914
01:07:20,245 --> 01:07:22,206
No. You two will never frolic.

915
01:07:22,372 --> 01:07:24,041
Why not?

916
01:07:24,124 --> 01:07:28,420
You see, in nature
there's a delicate balance.

917
01:07:28,587 --> 01:07:30,464
Oh, yeah. The circle of life.
I know that.

918
01:07:30,631 --> 01:07:32,257
- No.
- No, no, no.

919
01:07:32,341 --> 01:07:33,383
I don't know where
you're getting "circle" from.

920
01:07:33,467 --> 01:07:34,468
No, yeah.

921
01:07:34,551 --> 01:07:35,594
There's no circle of life.

922
01:07:35,677 --> 01:07:36,720
- No, it's no circle.
- No, not at all.

923
01:07:36,803 --> 01:07:38,972
- In fact, it's the opposite.
- Yeah.

924
01:07:39,139 --> 01:07:40,265
- It's a line.
- Yeah.

925
01:07:40,432 --> 01:07:42,935
It's a meaningless line
of indifference.

926
01:07:43,101 --> 01:07:45,520
And we're all just running
towards the end of the line.

927
01:07:45,687 --> 01:07:48,941
And then one day we'll reach
the end, and that'll be it.

928
01:07:49,107 --> 01:07:50,192
- That's it.
- Line over!

929
01:07:50,359 --> 01:07:52,110
- Nothing.
- Nada.

930
01:07:52,277 --> 01:07:53,445
And you can really
just kinda...

931
01:07:53,612 --> 01:07:55,322
do your own thing
and fend for yourself...

932
01:07:55,489 --> 01:07:57,282
'cause your line doesn't
affect anyone else's lines.

933
01:07:57,449 --> 01:07:59,660
You're alive and then
you're not. Like this guy.

934
01:07:59,910 --> 01:08:00,953
Mmm.

935
01:08:01,245 --> 01:08:02,871
You sure it's not a circle?

936
01:08:03,413 --> 01:08:05,040
That we're all connected?

937
01:08:05,207 --> 01:08:07,459
A circle would mean
we're all this.

938
01:08:07,626 --> 01:08:09,920
That would mean
what I do affects him...

939
01:08:10,087 --> 01:08:11,588
affects that thing,
affects that thing.

940
01:08:11,672 --> 01:08:13,131
Yeah. No.
That's not how it goes.

941
01:08:13,298 --> 01:08:14,925
Which would make
doing whatever we wanted

942
01:08:15,008 --> 01:08:16,218
not that cool.

943
01:08:16,385 --> 01:08:17,844
Let me simplify this for you.

944
01:08:18,011 --> 01:08:19,721
- Life is meaningless.
- Yes.

945
01:08:19,888 --> 01:08:21,723
That's why you just gotta
look out for yourself.

946
01:08:21,890 --> 01:08:23,267
That's why you do you, Simba.

947
01:08:23,433 --> 01:08:25,644
Yeah, Simba,
for the first time...

948
01:08:25,811 --> 01:08:28,105
we're entrusting you to
make a plan for us today.

949
01:08:28,272 --> 01:08:30,899
This is important. Think about
all you've been taught.

950
01:08:31,066 --> 01:08:33,026
What do you wanna do?

951
01:08:34,069 --> 01:08:36,863
Absolutely nothing.

952
01:08:38,407 --> 01:08:40,033
- Whoo-hoo!
- Exactly! He gets it!

953
01:08:40,200 --> 01:08:41,868
Jackpot!

954
01:08:42,035 --> 01:08:43,036
Out of my way!
Out of my way!

955
01:08:43,120 --> 01:08:45,747
- Crunchy!
- All right! Time to eat!

956
01:08:56,300 --> 01:08:58,385
Oh.

957
01:08:58,468 --> 01:09:00,554
Hello!

958
01:09:00,721 --> 01:09:02,556
Nice one, Simba.

959
01:09:02,723 --> 01:09:05,350
Oh, thanks.
Must've been the termites.

960
01:09:05,434 --> 01:09:07,352
Or the crickets.

961
01:09:08,770 --> 01:09:11,481
And you wonder why I prefer
to sleep underground.

962
01:09:12,149 --> 01:09:13,942
Hey, Timon.

963
01:09:14,109 --> 01:09:15,360
Do you ever look up there

964
01:09:15,444 --> 01:09:17,779
and wonder
what those sparkly dots are?

965
01:09:17,946 --> 01:09:21,658
Oh, Pumbaa.
I don't wonder. I know.

966
01:09:21,825 --> 01:09:23,827
Really? What are they?

967
01:09:24,161 --> 01:09:25,704
They're fireflies.

968
01:09:25,871 --> 01:09:29,875
Fireflies that got stuck on
that big, bluish-black thing.

969
01:09:29,958 --> 01:09:30,959
Oh.

970
01:09:31,168 --> 01:09:32,419
I guess that makes sense.

971
01:09:32,586 --> 01:09:34,546
I always thought
they were balls of gas

972
01:09:34,629 --> 01:09:36,715
burning
billions of miles away.

973
01:09:36,882 --> 01:09:39,217
Oh, Pumbaa, why is everything
always gas with you?

974
01:09:39,384 --> 01:09:40,802
I know.

975
01:09:41,219 --> 01:09:42,804
- What do you think, Simba?
- Yeah.

976
01:09:42,971 --> 01:09:45,182
Oh, I don't know.

977
01:09:46,266 --> 01:09:48,268
But somebody once told me...

978
01:09:48,435 --> 01:09:50,645
the great kings of the past
are up there...

979
01:09:50,812 --> 01:09:53,857
and they're all
watching over us.

980
01:09:58,278 --> 01:10:01,782
That's a good one!
That's insane!

981
01:10:01,948 --> 01:10:03,784
That's insane!

982
01:10:04,951 --> 01:10:06,953
Royal dead guys
watching over us!

983
01:10:07,120 --> 01:10:09,081
Well, I hope they don't
fall out of the sky!

984
01:10:09,247 --> 01:10:11,792
Hang on, Your Majesty!
Don't let go!

985
01:10:11,958 --> 01:10:13,293
Oh, that would be a mess.

986
01:10:13,460 --> 01:10:14,503
Oh, man!

987
01:10:14,586 --> 01:10:15,587
I mean, Simba,
think about it.

988
01:10:15,754 --> 01:10:18,090
Why would a bunch of kings
be looking out for us?

989
01:10:18,256 --> 01:10:20,258
- We're outcasts.
- Royal warthogs!

990
01:10:20,425 --> 01:10:22,969
- I can't! I can't!
- I can't! I actually can't.

991
01:10:23,136 --> 01:10:26,765
- I can't.
- No, you can. I can't.

992
01:10:28,183 --> 01:10:30,894
Yeah. Yeah.

993
01:10:31,061 --> 01:10:33,063
Yeah.

994
01:10:33,230 --> 01:10:34,773
That's stupid.

995
01:10:34,940 --> 01:10:38,944
I'm gonna go get some grubs
or something.

996
01:10:45,951 --> 01:10:48,495
- What did you say to him?
- I don't know.

997
01:10:48,662 --> 01:10:49,913
As you were saying it,

998
01:10:49,996 --> 01:10:51,373
I thought,
"This won't end well."

999
01:10:51,540 --> 01:10:53,792
- You just start laughing.
- You laughed too.

1000
01:10:53,959 --> 01:10:57,379
I did not. I would never.

1001
01:10:57,462 --> 01:10:59,464
Man, I blew it.

1002
01:14:05,066 --> 01:14:06,693
Simba.

1003
01:14:11,948 --> 01:14:15,577
Simba is alive!

