1281
01:31:39,495 --> 01:31:40,913
Hyenas everywhere.

1282
01:31:41,080 --> 01:31:42,373
I hope it's a quick death.

1283
01:31:42,456 --> 01:31:43,749
You know,
just not a lot of chewing.

1284
01:31:43,916 --> 01:31:45,000
What's your plan
for getting us

1285
01:31:45,084 --> 01:31:46,251
past the slobbering guards?

1286
01:31:46,794 --> 01:31:48,796
Live bait.

1287
01:31:53,133 --> 01:31:54,718
That's a great idea.

1288
01:31:54,885 --> 01:31:57,179
Those guys could never
resist fresh meat.

1289
01:31:57,346 --> 01:32:00,349
So all we need to do is find
something that's, like, big...

1290
01:32:00,516 --> 01:32:02,559
and plump, and juicy.

1291
01:32:02,726 --> 01:32:04,853
Maybe like a gnu?

1292
01:32:06,230 --> 01:32:08,357
Why is everyone looking at me?

1293
01:32:14,113 --> 01:32:16,323
It is with deepest pride

1294
01:32:16,407 --> 01:32:18,450
and greatest pleasure...

1295
01:32:18,617 --> 01:32:21,745
that we proudly present...

1296
01:32:21,912 --> 01:32:23,497
your dinner.

1297
01:32:26,041 --> 01:32:29,837
<i>Be our guest</i>

1298
01:32:33,173 --> 01:32:35,676
It's working, Pumbaa!

1299
01:33:08,250 --> 01:33:10,669
My old friend.

1300
01:33:11,420 --> 01:33:13,547
Sarabi,
why put yourself through this?

1301
01:33:13,881 --> 01:33:16,341
All you have to do
is be my queen.

1302
01:33:16,508 --> 01:33:17,968
You're suffering for what?

1303
01:33:18,135 --> 01:33:19,970
The memory of a life
you once knew?

1304
01:33:20,137 --> 01:33:22,139
A king you once loved?

1305
01:33:23,307 --> 01:33:26,685
I tried to make you understand
what a true king can be.

1306
01:33:26,852 --> 01:33:31,523
Scar, a true king's power
is his compassion.

1307
01:33:31,690 --> 01:33:33,776
I am ten times
the king Mufasa was!

1308
01:33:33,942 --> 01:33:36,528
You are nothing
compared to Mufasa!

1309
01:33:47,873 --> 01:33:49,166
Mufasa?

1310
01:33:49,333 --> 01:33:50,375
It can't be.

1311
01:33:50,709 --> 01:33:52,836
Get away from my mother.

1312
01:33:55,422 --> 01:33:56,840
Simba.

1313
01:33:59,259 --> 01:34:01,261
You're alive?

1314
01:34:01,428 --> 01:34:03,764
How can that be?

1315
01:34:04,014 --> 01:34:06,058
I'm here, Mother.

1316
01:34:06,225 --> 01:34:07,226
I'm home.

1317
01:34:07,392 --> 01:34:08,811
Simba...

1318
01:34:09,102 --> 01:34:11,230
I'm so happy to see you.

1319
01:34:11,313 --> 01:34:12,314
Alive.

1320
01:34:13,899 --> 01:34:17,778
Give me one good reason
why I shouldn't rip you apart.

1321
01:34:17,945 --> 01:34:20,030
I can give you more than one.

1322
01:34:20,197 --> 01:34:21,323
You see...

1323
01:34:21,698 --> 01:34:23,575
they think I'm king.

1324
01:34:25,911 --> 01:34:27,746
Well, we don't.

1325
01:34:28,914 --> 01:34:30,958
Your reign is over, Scar.

1326
01:34:31,959 --> 01:34:34,503
Simba is the rightful king!

1327
01:34:34,670 --> 01:34:38,215
If you wanna get him,
you have to get through us.

1328
01:34:38,382 --> 01:34:40,425
Are you with me, lions?

1329
01:34:43,804 --> 01:34:47,599
The choice is yours, Scar.
Step down or fight.

1330
01:34:47,975 --> 01:34:50,686
Must this all end in violence?

1331
01:34:52,187 --> 01:34:55,607
I'd hate to be responsible for
the death of a family member.

1332
01:34:56,233 --> 01:34:59,069
To feel the shame
of knowing...

1333
01:34:59,236 --> 01:35:01,572
I took the life
of someone I love.

1334
01:35:02,030 --> 01:35:03,574
I put all that behind me.

1335
01:35:03,740 --> 01:35:06,952
But have they
put it behind them?

1336
01:35:07,119 --> 01:35:09,913
Do your faithful subjects
know what you've done?

1337
01:35:10,080 --> 01:35:11,582
What is he talking about?

1338
01:35:11,748 --> 01:35:15,043
So you haven't told them
your little secret?

1339
01:35:15,377 --> 01:35:17,546
Well, Simba...

1340
01:35:18,088 --> 01:35:21,008
now's your chance to confess.

1341
01:35:21,425 --> 01:35:24,803
Tell them who's responsible
for Mufasa's death.

1342
01:35:33,020 --> 01:35:34,855
It was me.

1343
01:35:35,188 --> 01:35:37,024
It's not true.

1344
01:35:38,066 --> 01:35:40,027
Tell me it's not true.

1345
01:35:40,193 --> 01:35:41,904
It's true. I'm sorry.

1346
01:35:42,070 --> 01:35:43,864
He admits it.

1347
01:35:44,031 --> 01:35:45,032
Murderer!

1348
01:35:45,198 --> 01:35:47,075
No, no.
It was an accident.

1349
01:35:47,242 --> 01:35:49,161
If it weren't for you
the king would be alive.

1350
01:35:49,328 --> 01:35:51,872
It's your fault he's dead!
Do you deny it?

1351
01:35:52,039 --> 01:35:53,040
I'm not a murderer.

1352
01:35:53,457 --> 01:35:55,876
We should believe a son who
takes the life of a father?

1353
01:35:56,043 --> 01:35:58,462
We should believe a son
who takes the life of a king?

1354
01:35:58,837 --> 01:36:00,964
A son who abandons his mother?

1355
01:36:01,256 --> 01:36:02,633
No. I'm...

1356
01:36:02,799 --> 01:36:05,719
You're what? Say it!
Are you the king?

1357
01:36:05,886 --> 01:36:07,054
No. No, I'm...

1358
01:36:07,220 --> 01:36:08,472
- Are you the king?
- No, I'm...

1359
01:36:08,639 --> 01:36:10,307
- You're what? Say it!
- I'm...

1360
01:36:11,934 --> 01:36:12,976
I'm nothing.

1361
01:36:13,352 --> 01:36:14,811
Then bow to your king!

1362
01:36:17,689 --> 01:36:18,774
Simba!

1363
01:36:34,331 --> 01:36:36,458
This looks familiar.

1364
01:36:36,625 --> 01:36:40,921
Where have I seen this before?

1365
01:36:41,213 --> 01:36:44,049
Oh, yes, I remember.

1366
01:36:44,967 --> 01:36:48,053
This is the way Mufasa looked
before he died.

1367
01:36:48,136 --> 01:36:51,223
I looked down...

1368
01:36:51,390 --> 01:36:54,017
saw the fear in his eyes.

1369
01:36:57,771 --> 01:37:00,941
And here's my little secret.

1370
01:37:01,108 --> 01:37:03,986
I killed Mufasa.

1371
01:37:10,617 --> 01:37:13,245
No!

1372
01:37:18,166 --> 01:37:19,167
My father!

1373
01:37:19,501 --> 01:37:20,502
Your own brother!

1374
01:37:20,585 --> 01:37:21,670
How could you?

1375
01:37:22,004 --> 01:37:23,547
First he kills Mufasa...

1376
01:37:24,047 --> 01:37:25,507
and now he wants to kill me!

1377
01:37:25,674 --> 01:37:26,925
You killed him!

1378
01:37:27,092 --> 01:37:28,385
Tell them the truth!

1379
01:37:28,552 --> 01:37:30,095
Don't believe his lies!

1380
01:37:30,262 --> 01:37:31,471
Scar...

1381
01:37:31,638 --> 01:37:34,850
you told us you didn't get
to the gorge in time.

1382
01:37:35,267 --> 01:37:36,518
That's true!

1383
01:37:36,685 --> 01:37:39,855
Then how did you see
the look in Mufasa's eyes?

1384
01:37:41,690 --> 01:37:42,983
Murderer!

1385
01:37:43,650 --> 01:37:45,110
Kill them all!

1386
01:37:51,950 --> 01:37:53,452
Lions, attack!

1387
01:38:08,300 --> 01:38:10,010
Simba!

1388
01:38:15,682 --> 01:38:18,602
- Pumbaa, I think we lost them.
- That was terrifying.

1389
01:38:19,978 --> 01:38:21,646
Do you hear a low growl?

1390
01:38:22,481 --> 01:38:25,067
Looks like we'll be
having pig for dinner.

1391
01:38:25,233 --> 01:38:27,194
Plump and chubby.

1392
01:38:27,736 --> 01:38:28,945
Chubby?

1393
01:38:29,321 --> 01:38:31,364
- Did he just call me chubby?
- Uh-oh.

1394
01:38:31,448 --> 01:38:33,950
It sounded a lot like
he just said "chubby".

1395
01:38:34,117 --> 01:38:35,911
Which would be
a mistake because...

1396
01:38:36,078 --> 01:38:38,371
I will not be made to feel
ashamed of who I am!

1397
01:38:38,455 --> 01:38:39,456
Oh, boy.

1398
01:38:39,539 --> 01:38:41,333
I may run from hyenas...

1399
01:38:41,500 --> 01:38:43,627
but I will always
fight a bully!

1400
01:38:52,135 --> 01:38:53,512
- You feel better, Pumbaa?
- I do.

1401
01:38:53,595 --> 01:38:54,638
You got that
out of your system?

1402
01:38:54,721 --> 01:38:55,722
I did.

1403
01:39:10,278 --> 01:39:13,615
Now, this is a meal
I've waited my whole life for.

1404
01:39:14,449 --> 01:39:16,743
I've been waiting too.

1405
01:39:16,910 --> 01:39:18,870
And I'm not a cub anymore!

1406
01:39:24,042 --> 01:39:26,169
For king and country!

1407
01:39:28,797 --> 01:39:29,840
It's the bird!

1408
01:39:30,006 --> 01:39:31,383
I got him! I got him!

1409
01:39:32,968 --> 01:39:34,261
Tally-ho!

1410
01:39:34,427 --> 01:39:35,428
Oh! No! He's got me!

1411
01:39:35,595 --> 01:39:36,805
He's got me! Ooh!

1412
01:39:39,933 --> 01:39:41,351
Get that bird!

1413
01:39:46,314 --> 01:39:48,733
Please! Let's discuss this.

1414
01:40:21,016 --> 01:40:22,726
That never gets old!

1415
01:41:35,048 --> 01:41:36,258
It's over, Scar.

1416
01:41:40,303 --> 01:41:41,805
Have mercy.
I beg you.

1417
01:41:41,972 --> 01:41:43,390
Mercy?

1418
01:41:43,556 --> 01:41:44,849
After what you did?

1419
01:41:45,308 --> 01:41:47,102
It was the hyenas.

1420
01:41:47,269 --> 01:41:49,646
Those revolting scavengers
made me do it.

1421
01:41:49,813 --> 01:41:51,940
I was planning
on killing them all.

1422
01:41:53,275 --> 01:41:54,776
You fooled the hyenas.

1423
01:41:55,694 --> 01:41:57,279
Just like you fooled me.

1424
01:42:00,282 --> 01:42:01,574
Simba...

1425
01:42:01,741 --> 01:42:03,868
you wouldn't kill
your only uncle.

1426
01:42:05,620 --> 01:42:06,746
No, Scar.

1427
01:42:08,498 --> 01:42:10,041
I'm not like you.

1428
01:42:10,917 --> 01:42:12,669
Oh, Simba...

1429
01:42:12,836 --> 01:42:15,130
you are truly noble.

1430
01:42:15,297 --> 01:42:17,007
And I will make it up to you.

1431
01:42:17,173 --> 01:42:20,051
Just tell me how
I can prove myself.

1432
01:42:20,218 --> 01:42:22,804
Tell me what
you want me to do.

1433
01:42:25,056 --> 01:42:26,349
Run.

1434
01:42:28,727 --> 01:42:30,854
Run away, Scar.

1435
01:42:31,396 --> 01:42:34,482
Run away and never return.

1436
01:42:36,067 --> 01:42:37,402
Yes.

1437
01:42:38,194 --> 01:42:40,196
Of course.

1438
01:42:40,905 --> 01:42:43,116
As you wish...

1439
01:42:43,283 --> 01:42:44,534
Your Majesty.

1440
01:42:44,784 --> 01:42:45,910
Aah!

1441
01:42:57,255 --> 01:42:58,715
You can't win, Scar!

1442
01:42:58,882 --> 01:43:00,342
This is my kingdom!

1443
01:43:00,508 --> 01:43:01,760
My destiny!

1444
01:43:54,979 --> 01:43:56,272
My friends.

1445
01:43:56,439 --> 01:43:57,857
It will take some time,

1446
01:43:57,941 --> 01:44:00,402
but together
we will build our army.

1447
01:44:00,568 --> 01:44:01,945
"Friends", huh?

1448
01:44:02,445 --> 01:44:06,116
I thought you said we were
"revolting scavengers"?

1449
01:44:06,282 --> 01:44:09,202
Yeah.
That you wanted to kill us?

1450
01:44:09,369 --> 01:44:10,370
No.

1451
01:44:10,495 --> 01:44:11,663
No, let me explain.

1452
01:44:12,330 --> 01:44:14,707
I was trying to fool him.

1453
01:44:14,874 --> 01:44:16,334
We will rule together!

1454
01:44:17,585 --> 01:44:20,672
There's only one true thing
you ever said, Scar.

1455
01:44:22,966 --> 01:44:25,009
"A hyena's belly...

1456
01:44:25,176 --> 01:44:27,095
"is never full."

1457
01:44:33,143 --> 01:44:34,227
No!

1458
01:45:27,280 --> 01:45:29,324
Your Majesty.

1459
01:46:23,253 --> 01:46:25,380
<i>Remember.</i>

1460
01:47:15,763 --> 01:47:20,059
<i>Till we find our place</i>

1461
01:47:21,102 --> 01:47:24,897
<i>On the path unwinding</i>

1462
01:47:27,108 --> 01:47:30,528
<i>In the circle</i>

1463
01:47:32,071 --> 01:47:34,991
<i>The circle of life</i>

1464
01:47:37,785 --> 01:47:41,873
<i>Circle of life</i>

1465
01:48:26,209 --> 01:48:29,671
<i>It's never
too late to turn things around</i>

1466
01:48:29,754 --> 01:48:33,758
<i>Recover, unravel the path
to confound</i>

1467
01:48:33,841 --> 01:48:37,553
<i>The doubters and losers
that line up despair</i>

1468
01:48:37,637 --> 01:48:41,391
<i>Who tell you it's over,
you're goin' nowhere</i>

1469
01:48:41,474 --> 01:48:46,312
<i>It's never too late, I hope
It's never too late</i>

1470
01:48:49,190 --> 01:48:53,069
<i>It's never too late
to get back on track</i>

1471
01:48:53,152 --> 01:48:56,948
<i>To get at least some,
if not all of it back</i>

1472
01:48:57,031 --> 01:49:00,743
<i>I thought I was happy,
and sometimes I was</i>

1473
01:49:00,827 --> 01:49:04,330
<i>But sadness is just
as important because</i>

1474
01:49:04,414 --> 01:49:07,625
<i>Got to carry the weight
and hope</i>

1475
01:49:07,709 --> 01:49:09,210
<i>It's never too late</i>

1476
01:49:12,714 --> 01:49:14,424
<i>Never too late
to fight the fight</i>

1477
01:49:14,507 --> 01:49:16,634
<i>Never too late
to cheat the night</i>

1478
01:49:16,718 --> 01:49:18,511
<i>Never too late to win the day</i>

1479
01:49:18,594 --> 01:49:20,304
<i>Never too late to break away</i>

1480
01:49:20,388 --> 01:49:22,265
<i>Time will start
to move too fast</i>

1481
01:49:22,348 --> 01:49:24,058
<i>But time is now,
my friend</i>

1482
01:49:24,142 --> 01:49:27,770
<i>I'm a long way from the start
But further from the end</i>

1483
01:49:28,271 --> 01:49:32,525
<i>Oh, no, it's never too late</i>

1484
01:49:35,737 --> 01:49:39,574
<i>It's never too late
to get up off the ground</i>

1485
01:49:39,657 --> 01:49:43,327
<i>Don't have to be noticed,
don't have to be crowned</i>

1486
01:49:43,411 --> 01:49:47,248
<i>I did what I've done,
and I don't try to hide</i>

1487
01:49:47,331 --> 01:49:51,210
<i>I've lost many things,
but never my pride</i>

1488
01:49:51,294 --> 01:49:56,257
<i>It's never too late, I know
It's never too late</i>

1489
01:49:59,093 --> 01:50:00,970
<i>Never too late
to fight the fight</i>

1490
01:50:01,053 --> 01:50:03,055
<i>Never too late
to cheat the night</i>

1491
01:50:03,139 --> 01:50:05,057
<i>Never too late to win the day</i>

1492
01:50:05,141 --> 01:50:06,976
<i>Never too late to break away</i>

1493
01:50:07,059 --> 01:50:08,770
<i>Time will start
to move too fast</i>

1494
01:50:08,853 --> 01:50:10,563
<i>But time is now,
my friend</i>

1495
01:50:10,646 --> 01:50:14,484
<i>I'm a long way from the start
But further from the end</i>

1496
01:50:14,609 --> 01:50:19,030
<i>Oh, no, it's never too late</i>

1497
01:50:25,036 --> 01:50:26,704
<i>Never too late</i>

1498
01:50:33,753 --> 01:50:35,713
<i>I used to say
I don't have time</i>

1499
01:50:35,797 --> 01:50:37,507
<i>I'm sleepin' tonight</i>

1500
01:50:37,590 --> 01:50:41,469
<i>A day doin' nothin'
is doin' it right</i>

1501
01:50:41,552 --> 01:50:45,306
<i>No hurry, no hurry,
it takes as long as it takes</i>

1502
01:50:45,389 --> 01:50:46,933
<i>You might as well sleep</i>

1503
01:50:47,016 --> 01:50:48,935
<i>for all the difference
it makes</i>

1504
01:50:49,018 --> 01:50:52,772
<i>I didn't find love
or peace on the breaks</i>

1505
01:50:52,855 --> 01:50:56,651
<i>These aren't excuses,
but a string of mistakes</i>

1506
01:50:56,734 --> 01:50:59,612
<i>I won't go back there</i>

1507
01:51:00,488 --> 01:51:03,491
<i>Not going back there</i>

1508
01:51:06,911 --> 01:51:08,871
<i>Never too late
to fight the fight</i>

1509
01:51:08,955 --> 01:51:10,832
<i>Never too late
